      <p>The K6 still requires hand effort, and dense light roasts can feel demanding at espresso settings. But the effort usually feels worthwhile because adjustments translate into predictable changes in shot time. This matters when you are working with a non-pressurized basket and trying to stay inside a narrow extraction window without burning through half a bag of beans.</p>
