      <p>Its limitation is the same reason it is easy: the adjustment system is more straightforward but less granular than higher-tier espresso-focused designs. That is fine for pressurized baskets and for drinkers who prioritize convenience, but advanced non-pressurized dialing can feel constrained when a single click change jumps too far.</p>
      <p>For most people in this price tier, the Q Air is still an excellent decision because it lowers friction. You get repeatable everyday grinding, solid cup quality, and enough control to learn espresso fundamentals without fighting the hardware every morning.</p>
